{
  "type": "final",
  "thought": "I have enough context to propose the required operations: insert Green card boundaries in reliability-playbook around the requested sentences, create a Green's theorem note with card, and merge web into programming directory.",
  "plan": {
    "kind": "intelligent",
    "strength": "go-ham",
    "summary": "Insert Green card boundaries in reliability-playbook (before 'Use jitter...' and after 'Circuit breakers...'), create programming/greens-theorem.md with embedded Green card, move all web notes to programming/, and delete web/ directory.",
    "operations": [
      {
        "kind": "edit-note-content",
        "targetPath": "architecture/reliability-playbook.md",
        "payload": {
          "action": "replace-selection",
          "targetText": "Use jitter and backoff so retries spread over time instead of forming synchronized spikes.",
          "replacementMarkdown": "%%CW_CARD_START uid:Green%%\n\nUse jitter and backoff so retries spread over time instead of forming synchronized spikes."
        },
        "rationale": "Insert Green card start boundary before the specified sentence."
      },
      {
        "kind": "edit-note-content",
        "targetPath": "architecture/reliability-playbook.md",
        "payload": {
          "action": "replace-selection",
          "targetText": "Circuit breakers protect dependencies by stopping calls when failure rates cross thresholds.",
          "replacementMarkdown": "Circuit breakers protect dependencies by stopping calls when failure rates cross thresholds.\n\n%%CW_CARD_END uid:Green%%"
        },
        "rationale": "Insert Green card end boundary after the specified sentence."
      },
      {
        "kind": "create-note",
        "targetPath": "programming/greens-theorem.md",
        "payload": {
          "cardUid": "Green",
          "title": "Green's Theorem",
          "content": "# Green's Theorem\n\n%%CW_CARD_START uid:Green%%\n\nGreen's theorem relates a line integral around a simple closed curve to a double integral over the plane region bounded by the curve. It is a special case of the more general Stokes' theorem.\n\n\\[ \\oint_C (L\\,dx + M\\,dy) = \\iint_D \\left( \\frac{\\partial M}{\\partial x} - \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial y} \\right) dA \\]\n\n%%CW_CARD_END uid:Green%%"
        },
        "rationale": "Create a dedicated note about Green's theorem and embed the Green card."
      },
      {
        "kind": "move-note",
        "targetPath": "web/caching-primitives.md",
        "payload": {
          "fromPath": "web/caching-primitives.md",
          "toPath": "programming/caching-primitives.md",
          "moveReason": "Merging web content into programming directory."
        },
        "rationale": "Consolidate caching-primitives note into programming directory."
      },
      {
        "kind": "move-note",
        "targetPath": "web/http.md",
        "payload": {
          "fromPath": "web/http.md",
          "toPath": "programming/http.md",
          "moveReason": "Merging web content into programming directory."
        },
        "rationale": "Consolidate http note into programming directory."
      },
      {
        "kind": "move-note",
        "targetPath": "web/image-demo.md",
        "payload": {
          "fromPath": "web/image-demo.md",
          "toPath": "programming/image-demo.md",
          "moveReason": "Merging web content into programming directory."
        },
        "rationale": "Consolidate image-demo note into programming directory."
      },
      {
        "kind": "delete-directory",
        "targetPath": "web",
        "payload": {
          "deleteReason": "Directory empty after all notes moved to programming."
        },
        "rationale": "Clean up empty directory after merge."
      }
    ],
    "warnings": [
      "Moving notes from web/ to programming/ may break internal links pointing to the old paths. Update any vault-wide links afterwards.",
      "Inserting Green card boundaries in reliability-playbook will nest between existing card blocks; verify no interference with those card boundaries.",
      "Delete-directory on web/ will be executed only after all move-note operations succeed; ensure no other files reside in that directory."
    ],
    "referencedCards": ["Green"]
  }
}

